"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882422","Scotland Office","false","2018-04-18","<p>The specific campaign spend is commercially sensitive. Digital activity, including social media campaigns, are funded through the Scotland Office programme budget. This is published in the annual report and accounts.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-04-18T14:29:59.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882422/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882422/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882422/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-04-13","Sovereignty: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how much his Department spent on social media campaigns which used the audience targeting filter, Exclude: Interests: Scottish independence since 2010.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","135484"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882423","Treasury","false","2018-04-18","<p>HMRC is on track to start migrating customers from the current Customs Handling of Import and Export Freight (CHIEF) system to the Customs Declaration Services (CDS) programme</p><p>from August 2018. The CDS programme has delivered on all its critical milestone delivery dates.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-04-18T14:13:40.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882423/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882423/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882423/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-13","Revenue and Customs: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 21 December 2017 to Question 119327, Revenue and Customs: ICT, whether HMRC remains on track to start migrating customers from the Customs Handling of Import and Export Freight system to the Customs Declaration Service system from August 2018.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","135485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882424","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","true","2018-04-18","<p>The Consumer Green Paper was published on 11 April. It seeks views on how to ensure that modern consumer markets work for all, both now and in the future, including in the telecoms sector. Government will consider the responses to the Consumer Green Paper and, working with independent regulators including Ofcom, will publish a response detailing how they plan to further protect customers.</p><p> </p><p><del class="ministerial">Currently, the Unfair Terms in Consumer Contracts Regulations 1999 protect broadband consumers when they enter into contracts with a provider. Ofcom has the power to investigate communicate providers' compliance.</del></p><p><ins class="ministerial">Currently, contracts entered into on or after 1 October 2015 are covered by the unfair terms in consumer contracts protections in the Consumer Rights Act 2015. There are also protections under Ofcom rules (GC9.3) to ensure that conditions or procedures for contract termination do not act as a disincentive against changing provider. Additionally, Ofcom has the power to investigate communication providers' compliance and have an open enforcement programme on early termination charges: https://www.ofcom.org.uk/about-ofcom/latest/bulletins/competition-bulletins/open-cases/cw_01199.</ins></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-04-18T15:27:54.66Z","2018-04-23T15:12:27.843Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882424/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882424/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882424/answer","Stourbridge","Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882424/answer/previousversion/52496","Biography information for Margot James","10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-13","Broadband: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, if he will ensure that the forthcoming Consumer Green Paper sets out provisions to ensure that broadband exit fees are charged at a rate that is fair to consumers.","false","Biography information for Paul Farrelly","Newcastle-under-Lyme","Paul Farrelly","135486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882425","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department does not collect or hold these data.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government (MHCLG) is responsible for the Public Land for Housing programme. The aim of the programme is to release land with capacity for at least 160,000 homes in England from the central government estate by 31 March 2020. MHCLG is now monitoring the progress of sites sold through both the 2011-15 and 2015-20 Public Land for Housing Programmes, in order to estimate the number of homes under construction and completed.</p><p> </p><p>Affordable housing provision on any given site will be decided at a local level, by the local authority in line with their policies and local affordable housing requirements.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-04-23T12:26:00.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882425/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882425/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882425/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-13","NHS: Land","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to the Answer of 1 February 2016 to Question 24633, whether his Department has collected data on the number of units of (a) housing and (b) affordable housing built on each parcel of NHS land sold in London since 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","135487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882426","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-23","<p>Any decision on the AWACS (Airborne Warning and Control Systems) Capability Sustainment Programme) will be taken in the best interests of the National Security of the United Kingdom against current and emergent threats. It is too early to comment further at this time.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-04-23T16:03:19.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882426/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882426/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882426/answer","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882426/answer/previousversion/52600","Biography information for Guto Bebb","11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","AWACS","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 20 March 2018 to Question 132489, on AWACS, whether he plans to assess the effect on the UK defence industrial base of agreeing a foreign military sale in respect of awarding a contract for the RAF's airborne early warning aircraft; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","135488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882427","Home Office","false","2018-04-19","<p>The Home Office does not hold the information requested. Data on prosecutions are the responsibility of the Ministry of Justice.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-04-19T16:24:04.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882427/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882427/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882427/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-13","Drugs: Halton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people in Halton constituency were prosecuted for illicit drugs offences in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","135489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882428","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-04-18","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Decisions on the provision and operation of post boxes is a matter for Royal Mail, subject to fulfilment of any regulatory requirements set by Ofcom.</p><p> </p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-04-18T14:33:25.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882428/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882428/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882428/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-13","Post Boxes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many post boxes (a) have been removed from operation and (b) had their collection rates reduced since the Royal Mail was formally privatised.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","135490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882429","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Pre-Exposure Prophylaxis (PrEP) Impact Trial is a research study that aims to recruit 10,000 participants over its three years to address outstanding questions regarding PrEP eligibility, uptake and duration of use, and impact on HIV and other sexually transmitted infections.</p><p> </p><p>All oversubscribed sites are asked to direct clinic attendees wishing to access PrEP to the trial website where information is posted on the nearest clinic that is open to recruitment. The website is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.prepimpacttrial.org.uk/" target="_blank">https://www.prepimpacttrial.org.uk/</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-04-23T16:19:11.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882429/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882429/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882429/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-13","HIV Infection: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what guidance his Department is providing to people unable to access the Pre-Exposure Prophylaxis (PrEP) Impact Trial due to sites being oversubscribed.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","135491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882430","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>All mainstream state funded schools, including faith schools, must comply with the School Admissions Code. This requires all admissions authorities to publish admission arrangements, which detail how, in the event of more applications than places, allocation of places will be prioritised. Admission authorities may choose to give priority to children living within a designated catchment area, but not all will set a catchment.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-04-23T16:54:07.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882430/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882430/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882430/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-13","Faith Schools: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent estimate he has made of the number of school-age children who live in the catchment area of only a state-funded faith school.","false","Biography information for Crispin Blunt","Reigate","Crispin Blunt","135492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882431","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-18","<p>We have introduced fixed term tenancies for new council tenancies to ensure we get the best use out of our social housing stock and focus this valuable resource on those who need it the most for as long as they need it.</p><p>The Secure Tenancies (Victims of Domestic Abuse) Bill will ensure that existing lifetime tenants who need to move to escape domestic abuse and are rehoused by a local authority are granted a further lifetime tenancy in their new social home.</p><p>We will set out the circumstances in which local authorities will have discretion to continue to grant lifetime tenancies in regulations</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-04-18T10:41:37.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882431/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882431/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882431/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-13","Secure Tenancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether the Government plans to give councils the flexibility to retain secure tenancies as standard in local tenancy strategies within the regulations under the Housing and Planning Act 2016; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","135493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882432","Treasury","false","2018-04-18","<p>Around 1900 staff were employed by HMRC in Preston as at 28 March 2018.</p><p> </p><p>At this stage HMRC has not agreed the Preston staffing position for January 2019. HMRC will keep staff updated as plans evolve.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-04-18T12:59:54.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882432/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882432/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882432/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-13","Revenue and Customs: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many staff were employed by HMRC at the Tax Credit Office in Preston as at 28 March 2018; and how many of those staff his Department (a) estimates will be employed at that Tax Credit Office by 1 January 2019 and (b) planned to offer redundancy to, make redundant or offer jobs at other HMRC offices in Lancashire, Merseyside or Greater Manchester to.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Sir Mark Hendrick","135494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882433","Cabinet Office","false","2018-04-20","<p>My department has been allocated £49.4 million for essential EU Exit preparations in 2018-19. This will be spent on work to ensure departments have access to the specialist resource needed to deliver a successful EU Exit. As with all Reserve funding, finalised allocations will be confirmed at Supplementary Estimates 2018-19 in early 2019.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2018-04-20T10:53:29.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882433/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882433/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882433/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-04-13","Cabinet Office: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to the Written Statement of 13 March 2018, Spring Statement, HCWS 540, if he will publish a list of where the £49.4 million in EU exit funding for his Department will be allocated.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","135495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882434","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department has been allocated £21.1 million for staff to support essential European Union exit preparations in 2018-19. This will include ongoing work in all relevant areas of the Department, such as reciprocal healthcare, ensuring that the safety of both United Kingdom and EU patients is protected. As with all Reserve funding, finalised allocations will be confirmed at Supplementary Estimates 2018-19 in early 2019. There are no plans to publish a detailed list.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-04-23T12:27:04.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882434/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882434/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882434/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-13","Department of Health and Social Care: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to the Written Statement of 13 March 2018, Spring Statement, HCWS 540, if he will publish a list of where the £21.1 million in EU exit funding for his Department will be allocated.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","135496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882435","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office has been allocated £29.6m for essential EU exit preparations in 2018-19. This will be spent on strengthening it's contribution to the Goverment's work, enabling it to develop our diplomatic network so it is better able to engage with our European partners in support of a successful EU Exit. We will also strengthen our bilateral relationships as we prepare to leave the EU, and will increase our staffing in London to work on a range of related issues. As with all Reserve funding, finalised allocations will be confirmed at Supplementary Estimates 2018-19 in early 2019.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-04-23T12:45:24.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882435/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882435/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882435/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-13","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the Written Statement of 13 March 2018, Spring Statement, HCWS 540, if he will publish a list of where the £29.6 million in EU exit funding for his Department will be allocated.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","135497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882436","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-19","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend, the Minister for Defence Procurement on 16 March 2018 to Question 132371 to the hon. Member for Bootle (Peter Dowd).</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-04-19T16:04:25.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882436/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882436/answer","20180316_132371_MOD_Public_Expenditure.docx","WQnA extract on MOD: Public Expenditure","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882436/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","Ministry of Defence: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Written Statement of 13 March 2018, Spring Statement, HCWS 540, if he will publish a list of where the £12.7 million in EU exit funding for his Department will be allocated.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","135498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882437","Department for Education","false","2018-04-18","<p>The most recent data show that, for full-time undergraduate students domiciled in England, 4,600 fewer students were in receipt of equipment Disabled Students Allowances (DSAs) in 2015/16 than in 2014/15. The full data are available at <a href="http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/financial-support-awarded/england-higher-education.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/financial-support-awarded/england-higher-education.aspx</a>. The main reason for this fall is that the £200 student contribution to the costs of computer hardware took effect from September 2015.</p><p> </p><p>This government remains committed to supporting disabled students in higher education, both through DSAs and through supporting higher education providers’ efforts to improve the support they offer their disabled students. Alongside this commitment, we are keen to better understand the impact of DSAs on eligible students, including that of recent DSAs reforms. We have commissioned a research project to explore this – we will respond to the research findings when they are available in spring 2018.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-04-18T15:46:50.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882437/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882437/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882437/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-13","Disabled Students' Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the introduction of the £200 self-contribution for disabled students who are in receipt of disabled student allowances on (a) the take-up of the equipment needed to study independently and (b) trends in the level of participation of disabled students; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Sir Mark Hendrick","135499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882438","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-23","<p>The MoJ has been allocated £17.3 million for essential EU exit preparations in 2018-19. This will cover additional staff and other requirements to prepare for EU Exit preparations, funding to support judicial functions, and some technical preparations in Courts and the Legal Aid Agency. As with all Reserve funding, finalised allocations will be confirmed at Supplementary estimates 2018-19 in early 2019.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-04-23T16:55:05.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882438/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882438/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882438/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-13","Ministry of Defence: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the Written Statement of 13 March 2018, Spring Statement, HCWS 540, if he will publish a list of where the £17.3 million in EU exit funding for his Department will be allocated.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","135500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882439","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-04-20","<p>The Department has been allocated £0.4m for essential EU exit preparations in 2018-19. This will be spent on policy and legal work to ensure that Northern Ireland’s interests are fully represented, considered and managed across a range of subjects as the UK leaves the EU. As with all Reserve funding, finalised allocations will be confirmed at Supplementary Estimates 2018-19 in early 2019.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-04-20T11:19:23.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882439/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882439/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882439/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-04-13","Northern Ireland Office: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, with reference to the Written Statement of 13 March 2018, Spring Statement, HCWS 540, if he will publish a list of where the £0.4 million in EU exit funding for his Department will be allocated.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","135501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882440","Scotland Office","false","2018-04-19","<p>My Department has been allocated £0.3m for essential EU exit preparations in 2018-19. This will be spent on departmental work, so we can continue to prepare effectively for Brexit. As with all Reserve funding, finalised allocations will be confirmed at Supplementary Estimates 2018-19 in early 2019.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-04-19T10:18:39.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882440/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882440/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882440/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-04-13","Scotland Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, with reference to the Written Statement of 13 March 2018, Spring Statement, HCWS 540, if he will publish a list of where the £0.3 million in EU exit funding for his Department will be allocated.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","135502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882441","Wales Office","false","2018-04-18","<p>The Wales Office has used the £0.3 million in EU exit funding to recruit more staff to work on matters relating to EU exit.</p><p> </p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-04-18T11:54:09.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882441/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882441/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882441/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-04-13","Wales Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, with reference to the Written Statement of 13 March 2018, Spring Statement, HCWS 540, if he will publish a list of where the £0.3 million in EU exit funding for his Department will be allocated.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","135503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882442","Department for International Development","false","2018-04-20","<p>My officials and I have made clear to the Government of Bangladesh that any relocation of refugees must be safe, dignified and in accordance with international humanitarian principles, standards and laws. We have concerns and questions about the island’s fitness for this purpose and have raised those with the Government of Bangladesh. The UK Government has not been involved in plans for the proposed relocation of refugees to the island. We continue to work with our humanitarian partners to further understand this proposal and its suitability.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-04-20T10:05:44.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882442/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882442/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882442/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-04-13","Bangladesh: Rohingya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether she has made representations to the Bangladeshi Government on its proposed transfer of Rohingya refugees to Bhasan Char island.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","135504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882443","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-19","<p>Mr Hall has not recently requested consular assistance. However, we have been active in supporting him in relation to his work promoting human rights. Embassy staff have attended trial hearings and raised his case with the Thai authorities. We shall continue this work, and stand ready to provide consular assistance should he require it.</p><p>The British Government supports the right of human rights defenders to carry out their work without fear of harassment or reprisals. We also support full implementation of the UN Guiding Principles on Business and Human Rights.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-04-19T15:13:59.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882443/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882443/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882443/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-13","Andy Hall","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has provided consular assistance to the British human rights campaigner Andy Hall, who has been sentenced for defamation in Thailand.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","135505"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882444","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-23","<p>The delivery of open access sexual health services is mandated for all local authorities. Sexual and Reproductive Health Profiles have been developed by Public Health England (PHE) to support local authorities, public health leads and other interested parties to monitor the sexual and reproductive health of their population and the contribution of local public health related systems. The Department closely monitors the range of indicators and outcomes at national level. Progress continues to be made: for example, in 2016, more people than ever were tested for sexually transmitted infections and the number of people infected fell, the under-18 conception rate in 2016 was 18.9 conceptions per thousand women aged 15 to 17 years; this is the lowest rate recorded since comparable statistics were first produced in 1969, declining by 10% since 2015 and 45% since 2010. The United Kingdom is one of the first countries in Europe to witness a substantive decline in HIV diagnoses. In 2016, 5,164 people were newly diagnosed with HIV in the UK (3,938 men and 1,226 women), representing an 18% decline from the 6,286 diagnoses reported in 2015. The decrease was most apparent in gay and bisexual men. In this group, the number of HIV diagnoses reported steadily increased from 2,850 in 2007 to 3,570 in 2015, and then decreased by 21% to 2,810 in 2016.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-04-23T16:23:03.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882444/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882444/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882444/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-13","Genito-urinary Medicine: Clinics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the effect on the provision of services provided by sexual health clinics of moving responsibility for and funding of those clinics to local authorities.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","135506"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882445","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-19","<p>The British Government has consistently made it clear that we seek justice to be done for the Rohingya. In line with the recommendations of the UN Special Rapporteur on the Situation of Human Rights in Myanmar, the British Government is considering how to support better co-ordination between organisations collecting evidence and testimony in Bangladesh. We are discussing this with international partners.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-04-19T15:16:50.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882445/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882445/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882445/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-13","Burma: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he supports the creation of an independent body to (a) investigate, (b) document, (c) collect, and (d) analyse evidence of human rights violations in Burma.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","135507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882446","Treasury","false","2018-04-18","<p>The vast majority of parents have been able to apply for and use Tax-Free Childcare without difficulty. Where parents have missed out on the government top-up HMRC pay compensation to reimburse them.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-04-18T12:58:01.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882446/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882446/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882446/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-13","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the total payments made by parents direct to childcare providers due to technical issues experienced with HMRC's online service for tax-free childcare.","false","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","New Forest West","Sir Desmond Swayne","135508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882447","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-23","<p>NHS England has advised that interim arrangements have been put in place at the clinical commissioning group, which will allow for the chief officer to return to their post at the end of the secondment.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-04-23T16:16:05.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882447/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882447/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882447/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-13","Halton Clinical Commissioning Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 28 March 2018 to Question 134090, whether the previous interim chief officer will return to Halton Clinical Commissioning Group as interim chief officer after the end of the secondment.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","135509"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882448","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-19","<p>Guidance to Natural England on issuing licences to cull badgers for the purpose of preventing the spread of bovine TB advises that where culling and vaccination are taking place on adjacent land, applicants should take reasonable steps to negotiate an agreed approach to badger control operations along the relevant boundary with that landowner/occupier.</p><p> </p><p>Modelling suggests that over time culling will outperform vaccination alone, and for most farmers, badger culling is likely to be the preferred option. Some farmers and landowners may prefer to use vaccination to reduce the prevalence of TB infection in badgers. Licences to vaccinate badgers will therefore continue to be available.</p><p> </p><p>Defra provides grant support for badger vaccination projects in the Edge Area but this does not preclude farmers and landowners choosing to cull in those areas provided the robust criteria for a culling licence are met. We see a role for both badger culling and badger vaccination as part of a comprehensive and balanced package of measures to tackle TB in cattle.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-04-19T12:11:23.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882448/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882448/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882448/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-13","Bovine Tuberculosis: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of extending badger culling on the effectiveness of vaccination schemes operating in those same areas.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","135510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882449","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-18","<p>The consultation on draft changes to the National Planning Policy Framework closes on 10 May. Following this, we will consider whether further amendments are needed in the light of the comments received, including those relating to garden city principles.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-04-18T10:22:12.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882449/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882449/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882449/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-13","Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to his Answer of 26 March  to Question 133676, how he proposes to take forward the garden city principles, other than those of design, now that those principles will no longer be included in the National Planning Policy Framework.","false","Biography information for James Frith","Bury North","James Frith","135511"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882450","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-23","<p>This data is not available.</p><p> </p><p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has published best practice guidance for the diagnosis and management of irritable bowel syndrome (IBS). Prevalence in the general population is estimated between 10% and 20%. IBS most often affects people between the ages of 20 and 30 years and is twice as common in women as in men.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-04-23T15:41:58.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882450/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882450/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882450/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-13","Irritable Bowel Syndrome","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many (a) men and (b) women aged (i) 10-20, (ii) 21-30, (iii) 31-40, (iv) 41-50, (v) 51-60, (vi) 61-70 and (vii) over 80 years were diagnosed with irritable bowel syndrome in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","135512"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882451","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Foreign Secretary has not directly raised this issue with his South African counterpart, Foreign Minister Lindiwe Sisulu. However, we remain concerned about the high level of violent crime in South Africa, including in rural and isolated areas such as farms. Our High Commission in South Africa monitors the situation closely and is in contact with the South African law enforcement agencies. The South African Government assures us that tackling crime in all its forms is a high priority.​</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-04-23T14:27:13.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882451/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882451/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882451/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-13","South Africa: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his South African counterpart on attacks against South African farmers.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","135513"
