"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882495","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-20","<p>As of 17 April 2018, 976 Ministry of Defence civilian personnel are employed on an apprenticeship scheme. In addition, there are around 20,000 Armed Forces personnel undertaking apprenticeships at any one time.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-04-20T11:32:54.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882495/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882495/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882495/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","Ministry of Defence: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many apprentices his Department directly employs.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","135557"
