"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882500","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>We have raised the case of Ahmed Mansoor with the Government of the United Arab Emirates, most recently on 15 April, and will continue to monitor proceedings.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-04-23T14:35:23.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882500/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882500/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882500/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-13","Ahmed Mansoor","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Government has made representations to the Government of the UAE on the case of the Emirati human rights activist, Ahmed Mansoor.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","135562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882501","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-18","<p>The minimum qualifying age for Pension Credit is linked to women’s State Pension age for both men and women. Until November 2018, when men’s and women’s State Pension ages will be equalised, a man may qualify for Pension Credit before his own State Pension age.</p><p> </p><p>In couple cases, the income and capital of both members is taken into account. Accordingly, in a couple case where the man is the claimant, the availability of the female partner’s State Pension may be a factor in determining entitlement, depending on what other income they have.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2018-04-18T14:11:51.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882501/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882501/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882501/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-13","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment she has made of the effect of the increase in the state pension age for women on the entitlement to pension credit of men who are (a) married to and (b) live with those women.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","135563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882502","Cabinet Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Civil Service chose to adopt the Ban the Box initiative in February 2016. The Cabinet Office issued guidance for departmental recruitment and HR teams to support departments to ensure their recruitment practices were in line with the Ban the Box initiative. For many organisations, the guidance formalised the good practice which already operated across the Civil Service. Departments have processes in place to approve exceptions. The Cabinet Office have not asked Departments to report on exceptions to the Ban the Box Scheme in the last 12 months.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","135565","2018-04-23T10:38:55.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882502/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882502/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882502/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-04-13","Government Departments: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to paragraph 45 of the Government response to the First Report of the Justice Committee, Session 2017-19, HC 416, which Departments have reported on exemptions to the Ban the Box scheme in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882503","Cabinet Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Civil Service chose to adopt the Ban the Box initiative in February 2016. The Cabinet Office issued guidance for departmental recruitment and HR teams to support departments to ensure their recruitment practices were in line with the Ban the Box initiative. For many organisations, the guidance formalised the good practice which already operated across the Civil Service. Departments have processes in place to approve exceptions. The Cabinet Office have not asked Departments to report on exceptions to the Ban the Box Scheme in the last 12 months.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","135564","2018-04-23T10:38:55.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882503/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882503/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882503/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-04-13","Government Departments: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the Government's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882504","Attorney General","false","2018-04-30","<p>No Crown Prosecution Service (CPS), Serious Fraud Office (SFO), Attorney General’s Office (AGO), or Government Legal Department (GLD) advertised job roles in 2016 and 2017 included a declaration box for candidates to declare a criminal record.</p><p>HMCPSI had one new recruitment in each of these years. The tick box was included in the campaign in 2016, but was removed in 2017.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2018-04-30T07:07:13.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882504/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882504/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882504/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-04-13","Attorney General: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135566"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882505","Home Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>There will be up to £1 million in total for the anti-knife crime Community Fund in 2018/19 and it will be launched later this spring. This was one of the commitments in the Serious Violence Strategy, launched on 9 April, which also said there would be a further round of the Community Fund in 2019/20.</p><p>This is in addition to the £765,000 awarded in December 2017 to community bids across the country.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-04-23T16:38:55.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882505/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882505/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882505/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-13","Knife Crime Community Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much funding her Department has allocated to the Knife Crime Community Fund for 2018.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","135567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882506","Cabinet Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>No job roles advertised by the Cabinet Office during 2016 and 2017 were excluded from the ‘Ban the Box’ initiative.</p><p>The Cabinet Office embraces and encourages diversity across its workforce; therefore none of our job application forms either digitally or physically requires disclosure of criminal convictions, and therefore meets the requirements of ‘Ban the Box’.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","135607","2018-04-23T10:27:50.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882506/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882506/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882506/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-04-13","Cabinet Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135568"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882507","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department has implemented the measures announced by my right hon. Friend the Prime Minister on 8 February 2016.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-04-23T16:29:51.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882507/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882507/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882507/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-13","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135569"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882508","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-04-23","<p>All job roles advertised throughout 2016 and 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-04-23T13:14:56.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882508/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882508/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882508/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-13","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135570"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882509","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>The department is fully compliant with the Ban the Box initiative. No roles advertised in 2016 or 2017 required applicants to declare details of previous convictions.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-04-23T16:56:11.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882509/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882509/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882509/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-13","Department for Education: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882510","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-20","<p>Core Defra was already compliant with the ‘Ban the Box’ initiative when it was adopted by the Civil Service in February 2016. Therefore, in both years a) 2016 and b) 2017, 100% of advertised jobs excluded the criminal record declaration box.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","135603","2018-04-20T08:46:55.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882510/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882510/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882510/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-13","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135572"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882511","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union was set up in June 2016 based on Cabinet Office principles and guidelines and operates a recruitment process in line with the Ban the Box principles. Recruitment into the department from the external market commenced in November 2016, with campaigns run by Civil Service Resourcing, and all roles have been advertised in line with the Ban the Box initiative.</p><p><br>The Department for Exiting the European Union is committed to improving diversity of opportunity and creating an inclusive working environment that attracts the best talent from the widest possible pool.<strong><br></strong></p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","135602","2018-04-23T13:24:48.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882511/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882511/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882511/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-04-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135573"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882512","Department for International Development","false","2018-04-20","<p>DFID applies the Ban the Box initiative to all recruitment campaigns subject to any exceptions for jobs with specific security requirements.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","135601","2018-04-20T11:05:13.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882512/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882512/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882512/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-04-13","Department for International Development: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of job roles advertised within her Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882513","Department for International Trade","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department for International Trade operates its recruitment processes in line with the Ban the Box principles. We are committed to improving diversity of opportunity and creating an inclusive working environment that attracts the best talent and makes the most of potential skills and productivity of ex-offenders in the community. Our records do not indicate any specific exclusions in the period requested.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-04-23T12:18:31.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882513/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882513/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882513/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-04-13","Department for International Trade: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135575"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882514","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department for Transport facilitates all its recruitment through the Civil Service Jobs recruitment platform and has done so since March 2013. This platform does not ask for applicants to enter any criminal record history or declarations at the point of applying. The Department therefore has been aligned with the aims of the Ban the Box initiative from this time.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-04-23T14:29:29.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882514/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882514/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882514/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-13","Department for Transport: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135576"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882515","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-19","<p>The application form template used by the Government Recruitment Services (GRS), who manage all recruitment activities on DWPs behalf, does not ask about criminal convictions.</p><p>This particular question is only raised as part of the pre-employment checking for candidates who have been deemed successful at the last stage of the recruitment process.</p><p> </p><p>DWP are fully compliant with the ban the box initiative. Therefore, no advertised jobs were excluded in 2016 or 2017.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","135598","2018-04-19T10:40:08.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882515/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882515/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882515/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-13","Department for Work and Pensions: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of job roles advertised within her Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135577"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882516","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-19","<p>All roles advertised in 2016 and 2017 in the Department excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-04-19T10:57:40.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882516/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882516/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882516/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-13","Department of Health and Social Care: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882517","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>​All job roles advertised for UK-based staff in 2016 and 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-04-23T14:03:27.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882517/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882517/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882517/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-13","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882518","Treasury","false","2018-04-23","<p>The information requested could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-04-23T12:15:16.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882518/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882518/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882518/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-13","Treasury: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882519","Home Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>Business in the Community's Ban the Box campaign was formally launched across the Civil Service on 17 October 2016 and the Permanent Secretary for the Home Office has not agreed any exceptions to date.</p><p>The information on which roles may have requested this information in 2016 prior to this date is not held at Departmental level and a manual search of all records would incur a disproportionate cost.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-04-23T16:30:00.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882519/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882519/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882519/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-13","Home Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of job roles advertised within her Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the ban the box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135581"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882520","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-20","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not ask for details of criminal convictions at the application stage for civilian roles. Applicants will be asked to declare criminal convictions either at the interview stage or when a provisional offer of employment has been made as part of basic employment checks. This was the position in 2016 and 2017.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","135593","2018-04-20T11:33:28.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882520/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882520/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882520/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","Ministry of Defence: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135582"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882521","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-19","<p>100 per cent of roles advertised by the Department during (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative. The Department was compliant with the Ban the Box initiative prior to the Civil Service adopting the policy as a default position in February 2016.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-04-19T14:30:57.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882521/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882521/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882521/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-13","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882522","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-23","<p>On 8 February 2016, as part of a wider set of measures to support the rehabilitation of offenders, the Prime Minister announced that the Civil Service would not ask for details of criminal convictions at the initial recruitment stage, subject to any exceptions for jobs with specific security requirements.</p><p>Therefore, to ensure we have the best possible mix of talent and act to remove barriers for all individuals, including ex-offenders, the MoJ fully implemented the <a href="http://www.bitc.org.uk/programmes/ban-box" target="_blank">Ban the Box </a>initiative that aims to provide fairer opportunities for offenders to compete for jobs by removing the tick box asking about criminal convictions from application forms.</p><p>The MoJ implemented this initiative in October 2016 and removed the criminal conviction declaration ‘tick box’ to declare a criminal record from application forms at the front end of the recruitment process. If an applicant is successful, security clearances will be carried out prior to appointment (Applying Criminal Records Policy) and each case will be judged on its merits where such offences are identified.</p><p>Data prior to this date is unavailable due to a change in recruitment system in December 2016.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-04-23T15:35:26.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882522/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882522/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882522/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-13","Ministry of Justice: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882523","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-04-20","<p>The Department uses the recruitment services of the Ministry of Justice. The Ministry of Justice implemented the Ban the Box initiative in October 2016, and since then all roles have been advertised without the early requirement to declare convictions, i.e. the ‘tick box’ has been removed. Data prior to this date is unavailable due to a change in the Ministry of Justice recruitment system in December 2016.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-04-20T11:39:41.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882523/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882523/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882523/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-04-13","Northern Ireland Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what proportion of job roles advertised within her Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882524","Scotland Office","false","2018-04-19","<p>The Scotland Office does not employ staff directly. All staff that join do so on an assignment, loan or secondment from other government bodies; principally the Ministry of Justice and the Scottish Government, whose recruitment procedures are used to employ staff into the civil service.</p><p> </p><p>The implementation of initiatives such as Ban the Box would be a matter for the recruitment procedures adopted by the employing departments.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","135589","2018-04-19T10:21:26.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882524/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882524/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882524/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-04-13","Scotland Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882525","Wales Office","false","2018-04-20","<p>The Wales Office is not an employer in its own right. The Ministry of Justice (MoJ) provide employment and recruitment services on our behalf. To ensure the best possible mix of talent and remove barriers for all individuals, including ex-offenders, the MoJ fully implemented the Ban the Box initiative in October 2016. Data prior to this date is not available.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","135588","2018-04-20T12:06:02.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882525/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882525/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882525/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-04-13","Wales Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what proportion of job roles advertised within his Department in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017 excluded the box under the Ban the Box initiative.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135587"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882526","Wales Office","false","2018-04-20","<p>The Wales Office is not an employer in its own right. The Ministry of Justice (MoJ) provide employment and recruitment services on our behalf. To ensure the best possible mix of talent and remove barriers for all individuals, including ex-offenders, the MoJ fully implemented the Ban the Box initiative in October 2016. Data prior to this date is not available.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","135587","2018-04-20T12:06:02.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882526/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882526/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882526/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-04-13","Wales Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135588"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882527","Scotland Office","false","2018-04-19","<p>The Scotland Office does not employ staff directly. All staff that join do so on an assignment, loan or secondment from other government bodies; principally the Ministry of Justice and the Scottish Government, whose recruitment procedures are used to employ staff into the civil service.</p><p> </p><p>The implementation of initiatives such as Ban the Box would be a matter for the recruitment procedures adopted by the employing departments.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","135586","2018-04-19T10:21:26.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882527/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882527/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882527/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-04-13","Scotland Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882528","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-04-20","<p>The Department uses the recruitment services of the Ministry of Justice who implemented banning the box on job applications in October 2016.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-04-20T11:40:33.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882528/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882528/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882528/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-04-13","Northern Ireland Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what her Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882529","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-23","<p>On 8 February 2016, as part of a wider <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/prime-minister-outlines-plan-for-reform-of-prisons" target="_blank">set of measures to support the rehabilitation of offenders</a>, the Prime Minister announced that the Civil Service would not ask for details of criminal convictions at the initial recruitment stage, subject to any exceptions for jobs with specific security requirements.</p><p>The MoJ implemented this policy in October 2016 and removed the criminal conviction declaration ‘tick box’ to declare a criminal record from application forms at the front end of the recruitment process. If an applicant is successful, security clearances will be carried out prior to appointment (Applying Criminal Records Policy).</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-04-23T15:36:23.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882529/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882529/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882529/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-13","Ministry of Justice: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882530","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-19","<p>The Department was compliant with the initiative prior to the Civil Service adopting the policy as a default position in February 2016. The Department continues to comply with the Ban the Box initiative and as such there is no implementation plan required.</p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-04-19T14:32:29.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882530/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882530/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882530/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-13","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882531","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-20","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not ask for details of criminal convictions at the application stage for civilian roles. Applicants will be asked to declare criminal convictions either at the interview stage or when a provisional offer of employment has been made as part of basic employment checks. This was the position in 2016 and 2017.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","135582","2018-04-20T11:33:28.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882531/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882531/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882531/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","Ministry of Defence: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882532","Home Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Home Office already operates the ban the box policy in line with Cabinet Office guidance and does not ask for information about convictions at the start of the application process.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-04-23T16:26:19.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882532/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882532/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882532/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-13","Home Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what her Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882533","Treasury","false","2018-04-18","<p>HM Treasury has already ‘banned the box’ and does not ask people whether they have previous convictions during job applications.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-04-18T14:03:35.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882533/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882533/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882533/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-13","Treasury: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882534","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>​The Foreign and Commonwealth Office's (FCO) recruitment policies already comply with the Ban the Box initiative - none of the application forms used to recruit UK-based staff to the FCO require applicants to declare any criminal convictions.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-04-23T15:44:50.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882534/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882534/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882534/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-13","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882535","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-19","<p>In February 2016, the Civil Service adopted the ‘Ban the Box’ policy as a default position, when advertising job vacancies. Cabinet Office guidance was issued to departmental recruitment and HR teams to support the implementation of this policy.</p><p> </p><p>Civil Service Jobs does not ask candidates about their criminal convictions at the application stage so the Department was already compliant with the Ban the Box initiative.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-04-19T11:04:59.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882535/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882535/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882535/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-13","Department of Health and Social Care: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882536","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-19","<p>The application form template used by the Government Recruitment Services (GRS), who manage all recruitment activities on DWPs behalf, does not ask about criminal convictions.</p><p>This particular question is only raised as part of the pre-employment checking for candidates who have been deemed successful at the last stage of the recruitment process.</p><p> </p><p>DWP are fully compliant with the ban the box initiative. Therefore, no advertised jobs were excluded in 2016 or 2017.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","135577","2018-04-19T10:40:08.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882536/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882536/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882536/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-13","Department for Work and Pensions: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what her Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135598"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882537","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department for Transport facilitates all its recruitment through the Civil Service Jobs recruitment platform and has done so since March 2013. This platform does not ask for applicants to enter any criminal record history or declarations at the point of applying. The Department therefore has been aligned with the aims of the Ban the Box initiative from this time.</p><p> </p><p>It is only if an individual is successful in being selected for a role, that information on an individual’s criminal record is requested from the Government Recruitment Service on our behalf in order to conduct the required pre-employment checking.</p><p> </p><p>If an individual does have a criminal record, they are not automatically discounted from being employed by the department and it is for the relevant HR Departments to make a decision as to whether the nature of the offence would prevent the individual from being able to carry out the job role as well as the level of risk.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-04-23T13:22:32.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882537/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882537/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882537/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-13","Department for Transport: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport,what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882538","Department for International Trade","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department for International Trade already operates its recruitment processes in line with the Ban the Box principles. We are committed to improving diversity of opportunity and creating an inclusive working environment that attracts the best talent and makes the most of potential skills and productivity of ex-offenders in the community.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-04-23T12:19:54.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882538/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882538/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882538/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-04-13","Department for International Trade: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135600"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882539","Department for International Development","false","2018-04-20","<p>DFID applies the Ban the Box initiative to all recruitment campaigns subject to any exceptions for jobs with specific security requirements.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","135574","2018-04-20T11:05:13.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882539/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882539/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882539/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-04-13","Department for International Development: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what her Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882540","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union was set up in June 2016 based on Cabinet Office principles and guidelines and operates a recruitment process in line with the Ban the Box principles. Recruitment into the department from the external market commenced in November 2016, with campaigns run by Civil Service Resourcing, and all roles have been advertised in line with the Ban the Box initiative.</p><p><br>The Department for Exiting the European Union is committed to improving diversity of opportunity and creating an inclusive working environment that attracts the best talent from the widest possible pool.<strong><br></strong></p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","135573","2018-04-23T13:24:48.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882540/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882540/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882540/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-04-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135602"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882541","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-20","<p>Core Defra was already compliant with the ‘Ban the Box’ initiative when it was adopted by the Civil Service in February 2016. Therefore, in both years a) 2016 and b) 2017, 100% of advertised jobs excluded the criminal record declaration box.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","135572","2018-04-20T08:46:56.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882541/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882541/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882541/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-13","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135603"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882542","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>The department is already compliant with the Ban the Box initiative and, as such, there is no requirement for an implementation plan.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-04-23T16:41:40.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882542/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882542/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882542/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-13","Department for Education: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135604"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882543","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-04-23","<p>DCMS is committed to offering all applicants equality of opportunity to apply for job roles, to ensure that we attract and retain candidates with the most talent and potential. The DCMS recruitment process does not require applicants to declare unspent criminal convictions upon application.</p><p> </p><p>However, applicants are asked to declare unspent criminal convictions as part of basic employment checks when a provisional offer of employment has been made. Decisions concerning appointment to a post where an individual has a conviction history are made on a case-by-case basis using risk assessments.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-04-23T13:13:43.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882543/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882543/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882543/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-13","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882544","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department implemented on 8 February 2016 the measures announced by my right hon. Friend the Prime Minister on that date. Since then, no job adverts have asked for details of criminal convictions at application stage.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-04-23T16:30:15.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882544/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882544/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882544/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-13","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882545","Cabinet Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>No job roles advertised by the Cabinet Office during 2016 and 2017 were excluded from the ‘Ban the Box’ initiative.</p><p>The Cabinet Office embraces and encourages diversity across its workforce; therefore none of our job application forms either digitally or physically requires disclosure of criminal convictions, and therefore meets the requirements of ‘Ban the Box’.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","135568","2018-04-23T10:27:50.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882545/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882545/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882545/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-04-13","Cabinet Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882546","Attorney General","false","2018-05-31","<p>The application process for the Crown Prosecution Service (CPS), Serious Fraud Office (SFO), Government Legal Department (GLD), Attorney General’s Office (AGO) and HMCPSI does not include a declaration box for candidates to declare a criminal record.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2018-05-31T08:57:45.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882546/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882546/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882546/answer","South Swindon","Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882546/answer/previousversion/55028","Biography information for Robert Buckland","88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-04-13","Attorney General: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what his Department's implementation plan is for banning the box on job applications.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","135608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882547","Home Office","false","2018-08-13","<p>The available information relating to processing of all out of country visa (and in-country visa) applications against service standards, is published in the transparency data at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data#uk-visas-and-immigration" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data#uk-visas-and-immigration</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-08-13T13:49:09.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882547/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882547/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882547/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-13","Visas: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many out-of-time visa applications were (a) processed within the standard service time (b) processed after six months and (c) processed after twelve months in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","135609"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882548","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-18","<p>Of the 35 National Health Service trusts and NHS foundation trusts in the North West region 27 are signed up to the scheme. They are below as follows, shown by the quarter by which they joined.</p><p>Q1 2017/18</p><p>Cheshire and Wirral Partnership NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Liverpool Heart and Chest Hospital NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Q2 2017/18</p><p>East Lancashire Hospitals NHS Trust</p><p>Greater Manchester Mental Health NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Lancashire Care NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Lancashire Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Mid Cheshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>North West Ambulance Service NHS Trust</p><p>Pennine Acute Hospitals NHS Trust</p><p>Salford Royal NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Southport and Ormskirk Hospital NHS Trust</p><p>St Helens and Knowsley Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust</p><p>Stockport NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Tameside and Glossop Integrated Care NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>The Royal Liverpool and Broadgreen University Hospitals NHS Trust</p><p>The Walton Centre NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Warrington and Halton Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Wirral University Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Q3 2017/18</p><p>Wrightington, Wigan and Leigh NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Aintree University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Bolton NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Countess of Chester Hospital NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>East Cheshire NHS Trust</p><p>The Christie NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>The Clatterbridge Cancer Centre NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Wirral Community NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Q4 2017/18</p><p>North West Boroughs Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust</p><p> </p><p>The trusts and foundation trusts not signed up yet are:</p><p>Alder Hey Children's NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Blackpool Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Bridgewater Community Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Liverpool Community Health NHS Trust</p><p>Liverpool Women's NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Manchester University NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Mersey Care NHS Foundation Trust</p><p>Pennine Care NHS Foundation Trust</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-04-18T15:53:47.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882548/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882548/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882548/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-13","Sugar: Soft Drinks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, on what date did each NHS trust in the North West sign up to NHS England's voluntary scheme to reduce the sale of sugar sweetened drinks in NHS canteens, shops and vending machines introduced in 2018; and which NHS trusts in that region have yet to sign up to that initiative.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Sir Mark Hendrick","135610"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882549","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-04-18","<p>Just over 1400 people have visited the platform so far. Around 130 responses have been submitted. The platform will be open until 22 May, with the majority of responses expected in the final weeks.</p><p> </p><p>The platform forms one part of a wider engagement exercise. Government is holding a series of workshops around the country, the first of which took place in Birmingham on 11 April. Officials are attending meetings of stakeholders networks to discuss the Strategy and we have published a toolkit to support groups to hold their own conversations and provide feedback.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","135612","2018-04-18T12:47:42.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882549/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882549/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882549/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-13","Voluntary Organisations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many page views the online Civil Society Strategy consultation form has received since the start of that consultation.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","135611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882550","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-04-18","<p>Just over 1400 people have visited the platform so far. Around 130 responses have been submitted. The platform will be open until 22 May, with the majority of responses expected in the final weeks.</p><p> </p><p>The platform forms one part of a wider engagement exercise. Government is holding a series of workshops around the country, the first of which took place in Birmingham on 11 April. Officials are attending meetings of stakeholders networks to discuss the Strategy and we have published a toolkit to support groups to hold their own conversations and provide feedback.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","135611","2018-04-18T12:47:42.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882550/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882550/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882550/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-13","Voluntary Organisations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many responses his Department has received in respect of its consultation paper, Civil Society Strategy, published in February 2018.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","135612"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882551","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department for Business Energy and Industrial Strategy have received initial ideas for a Defence Sector Deal from the Defence Growth Partnership and intend to provide feedback on proposals in the coming weeks.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","135614","2018-04-23T16:27:16.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882551/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882551/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882551/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what role his Department played in the UK Industrial Strategy Defence Sector deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","135613"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882552","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department for Business Energy and Industrial Strategy have received initial ideas for a Defence Sector Deal from the Defence Growth Partnership and intend to provide feedback on proposals in the coming weeks.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","135613","2018-04-23T16:27:17.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882552/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882552/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882552/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the timetable is for the conclusion of the UK Industrial Strategy Defence Sector deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","135614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882553","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) working in partnership with the Departments for International Trade and Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy is committed to help the UK defence industry grow and compete successfully. This was reflected in our approach to the refreshed Defence Industrial Policy which sets out the further steps we are taking to foster an internationally competitive and innovative UK defence industry.</p><p>A range of work is taking place to ensure the UK has the right Radar capabilities to meet current and future threats while securing value for money for the taxpayer.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","135616","2018-04-23T16:28:12.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882553/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882553/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882553/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","Defence: Radar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department has taken to ensure the (a) sustainability and (b) competitiveness of the the UK defence radar sector; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","135615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882554","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) working in partnership with the Departments for International Trade and Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy is committed to help the UK defence industry grow and compete successfully. This was reflected in our approach to the refreshed Defence Industrial Policy which sets out the further steps we are taking to foster an internationally competitive and innovative UK defence industry.</p><p>A range of work is taking place to ensure the UK has the right Radar capabilities to meet current and future threats while securing value for money for the taxpayer.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","135615","2018-04-23T16:28:12.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882554/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882554/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882554/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","Defence: Radar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he has plans to support the expansion of the UK defence radar industrial footprint; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","135616"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882555","Department for International Development","false","2018-04-19","<p>Given the UN Compacts are focused specifically on refugees and migration, there may be limited scope to ensure the specific needs of internally displaced people are addressed within these particular frameworks. However, there should be common lessons to apply in terms of the importance of a longer term development response to displacement and we are considering other opportunities to raise the profile of the issue and galvanise international efforts in 2018. For example, the UK is supportive of the idea of a UN High Level Panel on internally displaced people to assess the effectiveness of the current response to internal displacement and galvanise further political and operational action. We are discussing this closely with other interested States and UN agencies.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-04-19T09:32:00.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882555/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882555/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882555/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-04-13","United Nations: Internally Displaced People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent discussions she has had with her counterparts at the United Nations on the inclusion of provisions on protection for internally displaced people in UN compacts on refugees and migration.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","135617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882556","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-23","<p>Our refreshed Defence Industrial Policy outlines the action we have already taken, and the further steps we will take to help the UK defence industry grow and compete.</p><p>The Government's Industrial Strategy also sets out how we will boost the productivity throughout the economy. Many of the themes in this apply to Defence which has an important role to play in promoting competition, innovation and exports.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-04-23T16:24:43.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882556/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882556/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882556/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department has taken to support the long-term viability of the UK defence industrial sector; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","135618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882557","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Ministry of Defence keeps its equipment requirements under continuous review to ensure it can react to the evolving Defence environment.</p><p>Industry has been invited to respond to a request for information for a transportable long-range air defence radar which could be operated in a range of environmental conditions.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","135620","2018-04-23T16:26:18.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882557/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882557/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882557/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","Defence: Radar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment his Department has made of the potential merits of procuring a deployable long range air-defence radar; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","135619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882558","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Ministry of Defence keeps its equipment requirements under continuous review to ensure it can react to the evolving Defence environment.</p><p>Industry has been invited to respond to a request for information for a transportable long-range air defence radar which could be operated in a range of environmental conditions.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","135619","2018-04-23T16:26:18.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882558/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882558/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882558/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-13","Defence: Radar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he plans to upgrade or replace the radar system to ensure a long range air-defence radar; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","135620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882559","Treasury","false","2018-04-23","<p>During 2016/17 academic year, provisional data shows the following apprenticeship starts for Mansfield, the East Midlands and England:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Mansfield</p></td><td><p>1,450</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>East Midlands</p></td><td><p>47,180</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td><p>485,500</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Annual investment in apprenticeships in England will be £2.45bn in 19/20; double what was spent in 2010-11. Treasury ministers engage with the Secretary of State for Education on a regular basis to monitor the Government’s public investment in skills, and the impact it has had on businesses. Since the introduction of the Levy, 86% of employers said apprenticeships developed skills relevant to their organisation and 78% reported improved productivity (Apprenticeships evaluation 2017, November 2017).</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-04-23T14:14:59.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882559/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882559/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882559/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-13","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the economic effect of the Apprenticeship Levy on businesses in (a) England (b) the East Midlands (c) Mansfield constituency, since the levy was introduced.","false","Biography information for Ben Bradley","Mansfield","Ben Bradley","135621"
