"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882565","Scotland Office","false","2018-04-23","<p>The UK Government has been clear that we are undertaking a comprehensive and evolving programme of analytical work, examining all areas of the UK economy.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-04-23T14:37:01.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882565/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882565/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882565/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-04-13","Land: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what assessment he has made of the effect of the UK leaving the EU on land prices in rural areas throughout Scotland.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","135627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882566","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-18","<p>Under the Food Information to Consumers Regulations (EU 1169/2011) it is a requirement that food information shall not be misleading, as to its country of origin or place of provenance, method of manufacture or production or by attributing to the food effects or properties which it does not possess.</p><p> </p><p>It is a key priority as the UK prepares to leave the EU to ensure there remains a robust and effective regulatory regime for maintaining the safety of food for the benefit of UK consumers and of the UK food industry. The Secretary of State has set out our ambition to develop a recognised gold standard system for food and farming quality, to ensure that we maintain the highest standards of quality and transparency for consumers and take opportunities to market British food across the world.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-04-18T15:35:14.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882566/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882566/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882566/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-13","Food: Labelling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to end the use of food labels which are likely to mislead consumers; and whether his Department plans to introduce mandatory labelling on the farming method used for (a) meat, (b) milk and (c) dairy products.","false","Biography information for Mr Paul Sweeney","Glasgow North East","Mr Paul Sweeney","135628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882567","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-18","<p>The Department’s £50 million Homeless Prevention Programme comprises of thee funds:</p><ul><ul><li><p>£20 million to establish a network of 28 ambitious Homelessness Prevention Trailblazer areas;</p></li><li><p>£20 million rough sleeping grant fund for 48 projects providing targeted prevention and early intervention for those at imminent risk of sleeping rough; and</p></li><li><p>£10 million for 8 Social Impact Bond projects to provide personalised support for long-term rough sleepers.</p></li></ul></ul><p>Milton Keynes submitted bids for all three funds. In response to their cross-authority bid with Luton and Bedford for Rough Sleeping Grant funding, they were awarded £624,000.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-04-18T10:56:44.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882567/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882567/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882567/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-13","Homelessness: Milton Keynes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what applications he has received from Milton Keynes Council for funding for (a) homelessness and (b) rough-sleeping projects since May 2014.","false","Biography information for Iain Stewart","Milton Keynes South","Iain Stewart","135629"
