"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882576","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-18","<p>Under the Food Information to Consumers Regulations (EU 1169/2011) it is a requirement that food information shall not be misleading, as to its country of origin or place of provenance, method of manufacture or production or by attributing to the food effects or properties which it does not possess.</p><p> </p><p>It is a key priority as the UK prepares to leave the EU to ensure there remains a robust and effective regulatory regime for maintaining the safety of food for the benefit of UK consumers and of the UK food industry. The Secretary of State has set out our ambition to develop a gold standard system for food and farming quality, to ensure that we maintain the highest standards of quality and transparency for consumers and take opportunities to market British food across the world.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","135639","2018-04-18T15:28:48.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882576/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882576/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882576/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-13","Food: Labelling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps he is taking to prevent food retailers from using labelling to indicate that animals not reared outdoors were reared outside.","false","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","Chipping Barnet","Theresa Villiers","135638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882577","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-18","<p>Under the Food Information to Consumers Regulations (EU 1169/2011) it is a requirement that food information shall not be misleading, as to its country of origin or place of provenance, method of manufacture or production or by attributing to the food effects or properties which it does not possess.</p><p> </p><p>It is a key priority as the UK prepares to leave the EU to ensure there remains a robust and effective regulatory regime for maintaining the safety of food for the benefit of UK consumers and of the UK food industry. The Secretary of State has set out our ambition to develop a gold standard system for food and farming quality, to ensure that we maintain the highest standards of quality and transparency for consumers and take opportunities to market British food across the world.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","135638","2018-04-18T15:28:48.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882577/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882577/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882577/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-13","Food: Labelling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to ensure that food labelling accurately indicates that  animals used to produce the meat were raised (a) indoors and (b) outdoors.","false","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","Chipping Barnet","Theresa Villiers","135639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882578","Department for International Development","false","2018-04-18","<p>At the time of responding to this question, the Palestinian Authority (PA) has not yet confirmed or announced that it will provide payments to Palestinian prisoners in Israeli jails directly. UK officials are in contact with the PA to monitor the situation and the British Consul-General in Jerusalem is planning to meet with a senior Palestinian representative as soon as possible to discuss this.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","135641 ; 135642","2018-04-18T16:54:00.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882578/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882578/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882578/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-04-13","Palestinians: Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the implications for her policies on UK aid to the Palestinian Authority of the decision by that Authority to pay directly the salaries of convicted terrorists.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","135640"
