"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882708","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union does not collect or publish its own statistics and hence our use of different classifications will be determined by the data sources provided to us by other Government departments.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Race Disparity Audit website displays data where possible using the Census 2011 ethnic categories, which includes Gypsy or Irish Traveller.<br><br></p><p>Office for National Statistics (ONS) and the Race Disparity Unit work closely together to further progress the harmonisation of ethnicity data across the Government Statistical Service (GSS) and to improve the coverage of ethnic groups including Gypsy, Roma and Travellers.<br><br>The Race Disparity Audit Inter Ministerial Group chaired by the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster discusses matters pertaining to the progress of the Race Disparity Audit, including on the collection of ethnicity data.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Details of Ministerial meetings are published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns, which are publicly available on GOV.UK.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","135771","2018-04-23T14:42:49.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882708/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882708/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882708/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-04-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Travellers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General of 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, and pursuant to the Answer of 3 April 2018 to Question 134113, on Travellers: Equality, what meetings he has had since 2016 with the Minister for the Cabinet Office on using the 2011 census classifications that differentiate Gypsies and Travellers.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","135770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882709","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union does not collect or publish its own statistics and hence our use of different classifications will be determined by the data sources provided to us by other Government departments.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Race Disparity Audit website displays data where possible using the Census 2011 ethnic categories, which includes Gypsy or Irish Traveller.<br><br></p><p>Office for National Statistics (ONS) and the Race Disparity Unit work closely together to further progress the harmonisation of ethnicity data across the Government Statistical Service (GSS) and to improve the coverage of ethnic groups including Gypsy, Roma and Travellers.<br><br>The Race Disparity Audit Inter Ministerial Group chaired by the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster discusses matters pertaining to the progress of the Race Disparity Audit, including on the collection of ethnicity data.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Details of Ministerial meetings are published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns, which are publicly available on GOV.UK.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","135770","2018-04-23T14:42:49.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882709/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882709/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882709/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-04-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Travellers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General of 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, what progress his Department has made in using the 2011 census classifications that differentiate Gypsies and Travellers.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","135771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882710","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Race Disparity Audit website displays data where possible using the Census 2011 ethnic categories, which includes Gypsy or Irish Traveller. The Department has provided data from the National Travel Survey on measures such as driving licence holding, household car access and the number of journeys made each year. However, the number of Gypsy or Irish Travellers in the survey is too small to show data for this group separately.</p><p> </p><p>The Office for National Statistics and the Race Disparity Unit work closely together to improve the harmonisation of ethnicity data across the Government Statistical Service and the coverage of ethnic groups including Gypsy, Roma and Travellers.</p><p> </p><p>The Race Disparity Audit Inter Ministerial Group chaired by the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster discusses matters pertaining to the progress of the Race Disparity Audit, including on the collection of ethnicity data.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","135773","2018-04-23T13:48:50.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882710/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882710/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882710/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-13","Travellers: Census","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General of 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, what progress his Department has made in using the 2011 census classifications that differentiate Gypsies and Travellers.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","135772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882711","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Race Disparity Audit website displays data where possible using the Census 2011 ethnic categories, which includes Gypsy or Irish Traveller. The Department has provided data from the National Travel Survey on measures such as driving licence holding, household car access and the number of journeys made each year. However, the number of Gypsy or Irish Travellers in the survey is too small to show data for this group separately.</p><p> </p><p>The Office for National Statistics and the Race Disparity Unit work closely together to improve the harmonisation of ethnicity data across the Government Statistical Service and the coverage of ethnic groups including Gypsy, Roma and Travellers.</p><p> </p><p>The Race Disparity Audit Inter Ministerial Group chaired by the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster discusses matters pertaining to the progress of the Race Disparity Audit, including on the collection of ethnicity data.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","135772","2018-04-23T13:48:50.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882711/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882711/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882711/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-13","Travellers: Census","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General of 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, and pursuant to the Answer of 3 April 2018 to Question 134113, on Travellers: Equality, what meetings he has had since 2016 with the Minister for the Cabinet Office on using the 2011 census classifications that differentiate Gypsies and Travellers.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","135773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882712","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-19","<p>There have been no meetings between the Minister for the Cabinet Office &amp; Paymaster General and the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions since 2016 on using 2011 census classifications that differentiate Gypsies and Travellers.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-19T10:47:11.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882712/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882712/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882712/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-13","Department for Work and Pensions: Travellers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, since 2016, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General of 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, and pursuant to the Answer of 3 April 2018 to Question 134113, on Travellers: Equality, what meetings (a) she and (b her predecessor have had since 2016 with the Minister for the Cabinet Office on using the 2011 census classifications that differentiate Gypsies and Travellers.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","135774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882713","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-20","<p>I refer the Honourable Member for Stretford and Urmston to the answer given by the Right Honourable member for Gosport, Stubbington, Lee-on-the-Solent and Hill Head in response to PQ3878 which stated:</p><p> </p><p>“<em>The Department does not currently report on Gypsies and Travellers separately. As a relatively small group it can be difficult to obtain reliable data for statistical analysis especially when claimants are not required to give ethnicity. The Department has raised awareness of amongst Jobcentre work coaches regarding the cultural aspects of gypsy / traveller lifestyles.</em>”</p><p> </p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-20T10:23:40.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882713/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882713/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882713/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-13","Department for Work and Pensions: Travellers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General of 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, what progress her Department has made in using the 2011 census classifications that differentiate Gypsies and Travellers.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","135775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882714","Treasury","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Race Disparity Audit website displays data where possible using the Census 2011 ethnic categories, which includes Gypsy or Irish Traveller. The Treasury is not one of the departments that has supplied any of this data to the audit but other departments have done so in respect to the public services for which they have responsibilities.</p><p> </p><p>The Office for National Statistics (ONS) and the Race Disparity Unit work closely together to further progress the harmonisation of ethnicity data across the Government Statistical Service (GSS) and to improve the coverage of ethnic groups including Gypsy, Roma and Travellers.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-04-23T14:56:21.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882714/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882714/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882714/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-13","Treasury: Travellers","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General of 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, what progress his Department has made in using the 2011 census classifications that differentiate Gypsies and Travellers.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","135776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882715","Treasury","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Race Disparity Audit Inter Ministerial Group chaired by the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster discusses matters pertaining to the progress of the Race Disparity Audit, including on the collection of ethnicity data.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-04-23T14:57:29.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882715/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882715/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882715/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-13","Treasury: Travellers","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General of 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, and pursuant to the Answer of 3 April 2018 to Question 134113, on Travellers: Equality, what meetings he has had since 2016 with the Minister for the Cabinet Office on using the 2011 census classifications that differentiate Gypsies and Travellers.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","135777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882716","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Race Disparity Audit Inter Ministerial Group chaired by the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster discusses matters pertaining to the progress of the Race Disparity Audit, including on the collection of ethnicity data. The IMG includes Ministerial representation from the Ministry of Justice.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice is actively supporting the Cabinet Office’s Race Disparity Unit, which is working with the Office for National Statistics to further progress the harmonisation of ethnicity data across the Government Statistical Service (GSS) and to improve the coverage of ethnic groups, including Gypsy, Roma and Travellers.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-04-23T15:37:31.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882716/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882716/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882716/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-13","Ministry of Justice: Travellers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General of 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, and pursuant to the Answer of 3 April 2018 to Question 134113, on Travellers: Equality, what meetings (a) he and (b) his predecessors have had since 2016 with the Minister for the Cabinet Office on using the 2011 census classifications that differentiate Gypsies and Travellers.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","135778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882717","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-23","<p>In the Government’s response to David Lammy’s review of the treatment of BAME people in the Criminal Justice System, the Ministry of Justice (MoJ) committed to publishing more and better data on ethnicity. As a standard, we seek to use 2011 census classifications in MoJ datasets, though in some instances, due to the numbers involved, it is often necessary to publish at the 5+1 level or binary white/BAME level.</p><p>The Race Disparity Audit website displays data where possible using the Census 2011 ethnic categories, which includes Gypsy or Irish Traveller. My department has provided available data on Irish Traveller and Gypsy/Roma groups to the Audit in relation to the criminal justice system.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-04-23T15:38:44.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882717/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882717/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882717/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-13","Ministry of Justice: Travellers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General of 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, what progress his Department has made in using the 2011 census classifications that differentiate Gypsies and Travellers.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","135779"
