"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874660","Scotland Office","false","2018-04-16","<p>All the Office’s social media posts are made available to general audiences in Scotland. Where posts are promoted, officials select the most appropriate and relevant audiences in relation to the post.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-04-16T10:46:22.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874660/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874660/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874660/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-03-29","Scotland Office: Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what criteria his Department uses to select the audience for social media advertising campaigns.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","134961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874661","Home Office","false","2018-04-18","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes information on the number of persons specifically detained under section 136 of the Mental Health Act 1983, including information on where the person is detained, and whether they are under 18 or aged 18 years and over.</p><p> </p><p>These data were collected on a mandatory basis for the first time in 2016/17, and are published as part of the ‘Police powers and procedures, England and Wales’ statistical bulletin, which can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2017</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-04-18T16:07:02.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874661/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874661/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874661/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-29","Police Custody: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people of (a) 16 years old or under and (b) 17-18 years old presenting in a mental health crisis were detained in police custody for over four hours in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","134962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874662","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-16","<p>Before 2016, data on detentions under the Mental Health Act 1983 were collected in aggregate form in the KP90 collection, which cannot be broken down any further by age or duration. From 2016, the information requested is collected, but could only be provided from the Mental Health Services Data Set at disproportionate cost.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-04-16T15:57:44.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874662/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874662/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874662/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-29","Compulsorily Detained Psychiatric Patients: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many people aged (a) 16 or under and (b) 17-18 presenting in a mental health crisis were detained in a Section 136 suite for over four hours in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","134963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874663","Treasury","false","2018-04-16","<p>The administration of the tax system, including where appropriate the repayment of tax or duties, is a matter for HM Revenue and Customs. It would not be appropriate for Treasury Ministers to become involved in the administration of the tax system in specific cases.</p><p> </p><p>As I mentioned in the debate in December, HMRC is doing everything it can to resolve the issue promptly and fairly.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-04-16T15:11:57.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874663/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874663/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874663/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-29","Roadchef: Employee Benefit Trusts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the oral contribution of the Financial Secretary to the Treasury on 19 December 2017, Official Report, column 1029, when he expects HMRC to reach an agreement with the Roadchef Employee Benefit Trust on the outstanding tax issues.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","134964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874664","Treasury","false","2018-04-16","<p>I refer the Hon Member to my written answer of 5 July 2017 (UIN 1465).</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-04-16T15:17:46.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874664/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874664/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874664/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-29","Roadchef: Employee Benefit Trusts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the dispute over Roadchef Employee Benefit Trust, what plans he has to regulate employee benefit trusts .","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","134965"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874665","Treasury","false","2018-04-16","<p>I refer the Hon Member to the answer I gave on 4 December 2017 (UIN 115660).</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-04-16T15:18:35.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874665/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874665/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874665/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-29","Roadchef: Employee Benefit Trusts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will issue guidance to HMRC on unjust enrichment as a result of the Roadchef Employee Benefit Trust case.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","134966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874666","Treasury","false","2018-04-16","<p>This information is not held centrally by HMRC in the form requested and so cannot be provided.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-04-16T15:17:00.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874666/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874666/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874666/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-29","Taxation: Repayments","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average length of time was for repayment in cases of (a) tax overpayments (b) tax paid in error (c) tax on illegal profits.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","134967"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874667","Treasury","false","2018-04-16","<p>The information requested is not available as taxpayers do not report details of the levels of their profits on which they pay tax that came from illegal sources to HMRC.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-04-16T15:13:26.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874667/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874667/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874667/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-29","Taxation: Profits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the amount of tax paid to HMRC on illegally obtained profits in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","134968"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874668","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-16","<p>The evidential basis for the effectiveness of badger culling in the Low Risk Area, where infection in cattle is linked to infection in badgers, is the same as in the High Risk Area - that is, the randomised badger control trial.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-04-16T09:43:34.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874668/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874668/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874668/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-29","Bovine Tuberculosis: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the evidential basis  is for the effectiveness of badger culling in reducing TB in cattle in low risk areas.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","134969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874669","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-16","<p>Any decision to extend the badger cull to the Low Risk Area of England and remove the annual ten area limit on badger culling will be made separately to the TB strategy review. The decision will be made following the conclusion and analysis of responses from the current consultations, alongside relevant scientific evidence and veterinary advice.</p><p> </p><p>The review, led by Sir Charles Godfray, will reflect on progress to date with the broad range of interventions to fight the disease outlined in the 25 year TB strategy. It will consider what additional actions might be necessary now to ensure other tools and interventions are ready to be deployed in later phases of the strategy, in order to ensure the Government maintains progress towards its target of becoming officially TB free by 2038. The review is expected to conclude by September 2018.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-04-16T10:52:17.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874669/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874669/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874669/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-29","Bovine Tuberculosis: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether the decision to (a) extend the badger cull in low risk areas and (b) remove the ten area cap limit on badger culling will be made after the conclusion of Sir Charles Godfray's review into the TB strategy.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","134970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874670","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-16","<p>The effect of badger culling on local ecosystems is considered by Natural England as part of its licensing of the companies responsible for carrying out culling operations. Where appropriate, Natural England imposes conditions on licences so as to protect wildlife or habitats within and around the culling areas.</p><p> </p><p>When determining the appropriate operation in any particular area, responsibilities under the Bern Convention are taken into account.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-04-16T10:41:52.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874670/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874670/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874670/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-29","Bovine Tuberculosis: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of extending badger culling on local ecosystems; and whether an extension is in compliance with the Bern Convention on the Conservation of European Wildlife and Natural Habitats.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","134971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874671","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-18","<p>We have not carried out an assessment of these proposals. There is a long established precedent of free access for local residents to deposit household waste at household waste recycling centres. In 2015, the Government made an order prohibiting local authorities from charging householders to deposit household waste at civic amenity sites or household waste recycling centres.</p><p> </p><p>Where local authorities charge for the deposit of non-household items at Household Waste Recycling Centres, this should be done in line with the Controlled Waste (England and Wales) Regulations 2012. Where charges are proposed, they should be proportionate and transparent and made in consultation with local residents so that local services meet local needs.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","134886","2018-04-18T17:36:14.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874671/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874671/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874671/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-29","Waste Management: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment he has made of whether proposals by Norfolk County Council to introduce charges for DIY waste are compliant with his Department's policies on household waste; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","134972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874672","Department for Education","false","2018-04-19","<p>The Advanced Maths Premium provides schools and colleges with £600 per year for every additional pupil studying advanced mathematics post-16. It is a short term measure to support schools and colleges to tackle the barriers to increasing participation particularly in areas where take-up is currently low. This approach aims to support and encourage schools and colleges to continue to expand their mathematics curriculum above current levels.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-04-19T14:53:05.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874672/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874672/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874672/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-29","Pupil Premium: Mathematics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of extending the advanced maths premium to cover all pupils studying level 3 maths.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","134973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874673","Department for International Development","false","2018-04-16","<p>DFID will assess the potential merits and viability of enabling departmental staff to contribute to a credit union via payroll if at any time we receive a request from our employees to provide such a facility.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-04-16T16:43:01.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874673/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874673/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/874673/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-03-29","Department for International Development: Payroll Deduction Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 28 March 2018 to Question 134106, on Department for International Development: Payroll Reduction Scheme, if she will assess the potential merits of enabling departmental staff to contribute to a credit union via payroll; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Sir Mark Hendrick","134974"
